-- в”Ђв”Ђ MoEngage в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$MoEngage is an AI-powered customer engagement platform that orchestrates personalized cross-channel campaigns across email, push, SMS, WhatsApp, in-app, and web.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Custom (Growth plan reported from around $4,999/month)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$1,000+ employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, United States (dual HQ with Bengaluru, India)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$MoEngage Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$MoEngage review 2026: an AI-driven customer engagement platform for email, push, SMS and WhatsApp campaigns. Features, pricing tiers, and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$MoEngage is a customer engagement platform (CEP) that helps product, growth, and marketing teams orchestrate personalized, cross-channel campaigns across email, push notifications, SMS, WhatsApp Business API, in-app messages, and web push. The company was founded in 2014 in Bengaluru, India by Raviteja Dodda and Yashwanth Kumar, and has since grown into a dual-headquartered company with offices in San Francisco and Bengaluru, alongside additional regional offices. MoEngage has raised a total of roughly $458 million in funding across multiple rounds, with investors including A91 Partners, ChrysCapital, Dragon Funds, Mars Growth Capital, and Schroders, among others, and the company has reported hundreds of millions of dollars in annual revenue. Architecturally, MoEngage combines a customer data platform layer, which unifies behavioral, demographic, and transactional data into a single customer view, with a campaign orchestration engine and an AI layer branded Sherpa AI that powers send-time optimization, churn prediction, and real-time personalization decisions. The platform's segmentation engine lets marketers build audiences from live behavioral and demographic data, and its drag-and-drop journey and campaign builder supports complex, multi-step, multi-channel campaigns without requiring code. Core features include unlimited multi-channel messaging (email, SMS, push, in-app, WhatsApp, web push) on its higher tiers, AI-driven predictive analytics and churn prediction, customer journey analytics, real-time transactional alerts, A/B testing, and enterprise governance features such as role-based access, audit logs, and PII encryption. MoEngage uses a custom, quote-based pricing model driven primarily by Monthly Tracked Users (MTU) or Monthly Active Users (MAU) rather than a flat per-seat fee, and it offers two primary published tiers: Growth, aimed at rapidly scaling brands, reported starting around $4,999 to $5,999 per month depending on MAU volume; and Enterprise, aimed at large organizations with millions of users, reported starting around $19,999+ per month and adding full AI orchestration, dedicated SLAs, and compliance controls. Most MoEngage contracts carry a minimum one-year commitment, and add-ons like customer journey analytics and AI offer decisioning are sold separately. MoEngage's target audience spans consumer apps, e-commerce, fintech, media, and retail brands that need to run high-volume, personalized lifecycle marketing at scale, particularly in mobile-first markets. Its main competitors include Braze, Clevertap, Iterable, WebEngage, and Netcore, with MoEngage often positioned as a strong option for teams prioritizing AI-driven personalization and value in emerging markets like India and Southeast Asia alongside its US and European presence.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'e8e2b2b1-e626-4b69-b056-d2cfa9a442ef';

